### Summit VMS — REST API smoke tests
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP client.
@host = https://localhost:5001

### 1. Log in as an Investigator (can manage victims)
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "investigator@summit.gov",
  "password": "Invest#12345"
}

### Capture the token from the response above, then set it here:
@token = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 2. Who am I?
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. List victims (allowed for all four roles)
GET {{host}}/api/victims
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Get a single victim (audited)
GET {{host}}/api/victims/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Create a victim (Administrator / Investigator only)
POST {{host}}/api/victims
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "referenceNumber": "L200",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "Subject",
  "gender": 1,
  "city": "Central",
  "state": "NY",
  "notes": "Created via API."
}

### 6. List cases
GET {{host}}/api/cases
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
### --- View-only role demonstration ---
### Log in as the Home Minister (view-only).
# @name ministerLogin
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "minister@summit.gov",
  "password": "Minister#12345"
}

@ministerToken = {{ministerLogin.response.body.accessToken}}

### Minister CAN view victims:
GET {{host}}/api/victims
Authorization: Bearer {{ministerToken}}

### Minister CANNOT create — expect HTTP 403 Forbidden:
POST {{host}}/api/victims
Authorization: Bearer {{ministerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "referenceNumber": "L999",
  "firstName": "Should",
  "lastName": "Fail"
}
